sentences.content: This most basic pattern and includes just a subject and a verb.
Only intransitive verbs can be used to form this pattern.
The next most basic pattern combines a subject, a verb and an obligatory direct object.
Only transitive verbs can be used to form this pattern.

heading.content: Subject-Verb-Noun. Examples: I am the teacher.

sentences.content: The following practice combines a list of personal pronouns with the most common intransitive verbs.
If the verb is transitive, a direct object must follow the verb.

headingList.title: Subject-Verb-Noun. Examples: I am the teacher.
